{"body": "That would be really sweet (if i completely understood it). \r\n\r\nIf I dont want an ORM, I would use --skip-active-record as an option when creating the app. \r\n\r\nSo you mean to say, we hack around the [vicinity](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/master/railties/lib/rails/generators/resource_helpers.rb#L59). \r\n\r\nAre we saying we're going to quietly do nothing when the \"hook_for :orm\" is invoked?\r\n\r\nI definitely do understand the strategy but the implementation escapes me. Kindly guide. Once this is clear, then the skipping of test_framework will be clear too.\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1111228", "created_at": "2011-05-06T13:20:22Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/414#issuecomment-1111228", "updated_at": "2011-05-06T13:20:22Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 414, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/asanghi", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/f4ba063457702c78a7fce6a3529aedb0?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F06997f04a7db92466a2baa6ebc8b872d.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/received_events", "gravatar_id": "f4ba063457702c78a7fce6a3529aedb0", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "asanghi", "type": "User", "id": 762, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asanghi/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386091bd3543c15101228c"}, "id": 1111228, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/41